The `nums` array should have its indices starting from 0.The array `nums` should have a length of `n`.The integer `k` for the input should be provided.The count of pairs `(i, j)` where `0 <= i < j < n` should be returned as the output.The condition `nums[i] == nums[j]` should be satisfied by the pairs `(i ,  j)` in the parameter array, where the parameter array is the array `nums` passed to the method public int countPairs(int[] nums, int k).The condition `(i initial prepare . sh run . sh j)` being divisible by `k` should be satisfied by the pairs `(i ,  j)` in the method public int countPairs(int[] nums, int k) where the parameter array `nums` is sorted in ascending order.